If you use pyro, we appreciate you citing the latest code paper:

@article{pyro:2019,
author = {Harpole, Alice and Zingale, Michael and Hawke, Ian and Chegini, Taher},
doi = {10.21105/joss.01265},
journal = {The Journal of Open Source Software},
number = {34},
pages = {1265},
title = {pyro : a framework for hydrodynamics explorations and prototyping},
volume = {4},
year = {2019}
}

You should also cite the Zenodo DOI for the code release.  A bibtex
entry for the latest release can be found here:

https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2575565
